fields.description:
I have created a Maven 2 plugin that needs to create a zip file. The ZipArchiver fits my need much better than what the JDK provides, so I'd like to use this component. Unfortunately, I get the follow error when trying to run the code:

java.lang.IncompatibleClassChangeError
        at org.codehaus.plexus.archiver.zip.AbstractZipArchiver.createArchiveMain(AbstractZipArchiver.java:318)
        at org.codehaus.plexus.archiver.zip.AbstractZipArchiver.execute(AbstractZipArchiver.java:242)
        at org.codehaus.plexus.archiver.AbstractArchiver.createArchive(AbstractArchiver.java:673)

Here is the code I'm running:

		ZipArchiver zip = new ZipArchiver();
		try {
			zip.addDirectory( new File( project.getBuild().getDirectory() + "/rbundles" ) );
			zip.setDestFile( toFile );
			zip.createArchive();
		} catch( Exception e ) {
			throw new MojoFailureException( "Creating zip file " + zipFile + " failed: "
					+ e.getMessage() );
		}

I've tried 1.0-alpha-9 and 1.0-alpha-8, both give the same result. The offending line in AbstractZipArchiver is

        getLogger().info( action + archiveType + ": " + zipFile.getAbsolutePath() );

I'm suspecting that the problem is that the Maven 2 plugin uses log4j 1.2.13, while Plexus uses an earlier version (1.2.8?). My simple workaround is to comment out all log statements from AbstractZipArchiver, but it's not a sustainable solution...

Is there any way to upgrade the log4j version used by Plexus to 1.2.13 - or is there another way around this that doesn't require code changes (e.g. can Plexus be configured to use JDK logging instead of log4j)?
